Memoreve Privacy Policy
At Memoreve, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information about you when you use our mobile application and related services (collectively, the "Services"). By using the Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
Information We Collect
​
We do not collect any information from you through the Services. However, our servers may log IP addresses in order to maintain and improve the performance and security of the Services.
Use of Information
​
The information we collect is used only to maintain and improve the performance and security of the Services. We do not use this information to identify or track individual users.
Disclosure of Information
​
We do not disclose any information to third parties. We may, however, be required to disclose information in response to a court order, subpoena, or other legal process.
Security
​
We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction. However, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee that information will not be accessed, disclosed, or destroyed in the event of a breach of our security measures.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
​
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will provide notice by posting a notice on our website or within the Services. Your continued use of the Services after the effective date of the updated Privacy Policy constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.
Contact Us
​
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
